p%3EThe%20three%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fspace-force%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESpace%20Force%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20Guardians%20traveled%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fbase-guide%2Ffort-bliss%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFort%20Bliss%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20El%20Paso%2C%20Texas%2C%20to%20complete%20an%20Army%20Cavalry%20Spur%20Ride%2C%20a%20series%20of%20arduous%20combat%20tests%20and%20physical%20training%20exercises%20in%20which%20service%20members%20often%20ruck-march%20in%20between%20challenges%20%E2%80%94%20the%20first%20members%20of%20the%20military's%20newest%20and%20smallest%20service%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpace%20Force%20Capt.%20Bradley%20Evans%2C%20an%20engineer%20at%20White%20Sands%20Missile%20Range%20who%20took%20part%20in%20the%20Spur%20Ride%2C%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20all%20of%20the%20Guardians%20who%20participated%20completed%20the%20challenges%2C%20though%20some%20Army%20soldiers%20didn't%20make%20it%20through.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeing%20in%20the%20Space%20Force%2C%20we%20certainly%20received%20a%20lot%20more%20attention%20from%20the%20cadre%20than%20some%20of%20the%20soldiers%20did%2C%20which%20made%20it%20quite%20a%20good%20challenge%20for%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Evans%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20there%20was%20an%20expectation%20by%20some%20that%20we%20wouldn't%20make%20it%2C%20and%20so%20pushing%20back%20against%20that%20expectation%20and%20performing%20was%20a%20powerful%20driver.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20Space%20Force%20officer%20in%20uniform%20is%20covered%20in%20dust%20while%20carrying%20a%20firearm%20and%20holding%20a%20canteen%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663a8624b4abc992e8c6a071%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22642%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Space%20Force%20spur%20ride%20candidate%20hydrates%20during%20a%20spur%20ride%20at%20Fort%20Bliss%2C%20Texas.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Spc.%20David%20Poleski%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EEarning%20your%20spurs%20is%20a%20long-standing%20tradition%20that%20dates%20back%20to%20the%20early%20days%20of%20the%20Army%20cavalry%20when%20new%20soldiers%20had%20to%20prove%20their%20skills%20in%20swordsmanship%20and%20horseback%20riding.%20Even%20though%20the%20US%20military%20is%20changing%2C%20including%20the%20addition%20of%20the%20Space%20Force%20and%20its%20Guardians%2C%20those%20traditions%20are%20still%20upheld%20through%20rigorous%20physical%20challenges%20and%20training.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuardians%20are%20often%20deployed%20in%20place%2C%20meaning%20they're%20at%20military%20installations%20in%20front%20of%20a%20computer%20and%20not%20typically%20put%20into%20austere%20and%20deadly%20conditions.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20the%20service%20has%20placed%20a%20different%20focus%20on%20routine%20physical%20training.%20It%20has%20announced%20plans%20to%20use%20wearable%20fitness%20technology%20and%20take%20a%20more%20holistic%20approach%20to%20keeping%20its%20service%20members%20in%20shape%20compared%20to%20the%20other%20branches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20the%20Space%20Force%20officers%20who%20participated%20in%20the%20Spur%20Ride%2C%20including%201st%20Lt.%20Jordan%20Savage%2C%20an%20acquisitions%20officer%20at%20Space%20Systems%20Command%20in%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20physical%20challenge%20was%20vastly%20different%20from%20their%20day%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20Garmin%20captured%20us%20doing%20about%2037%20miles%20of%20rucking.%20We%20had%20a%2060-pound%20ruck%20that%20we%20were%20with%20the%20whole%20time%20that%20had%20all%20of%20our%20gear%20that%20was%20necessary%20for%20the%20Spur%20Ride%20and%2C%20on%20top%20of%20that%2C%20we%20had%20minimal%20sleep%2C%26quot%3B%20Savage%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20all%20those%20things%20are%20not%20what%20we%20experienced%20in%20our%20day-to-day%20life%20as%20acquisitions%20%5Bofficers%5D%20or%20engineers%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22US%20Space%20Force%20spur%20ride%20candidates%20crawl%20in%20the%20sand%20during%20an%20exercise%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663a86c5b4abc992e8c6a174%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Space%20Force%20spur%20ride%20candidates%20move%20a%20litter%20with%20a%20BGM-71%20TOW%2C%20low%20crawling%20through%20the%20sand%20at%20Fort%20Bliss%2C%20Texas.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Spc.%20David%20Poleski%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20Army%20soldiers%20who%20participated%20in%20the%20Spur%20Ride%20had%20never%20met%20someone%20in%20the%20Space%20Force%20before%20and%20quickly%20recognized%20cultural%20differences%20between%20the%20service%20branches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20many%20soldiers%20had%20questions%20because%20the%20Space%20Force%20is%20still%20so%20new%2C%20and%20they%20just%20want%20to%20know%2C%20'Hey%2C%20what%20do%20you%20guys%20do%3F'%26quot%3B%201st%20Lt.%20Jackson%20Jennings%2C%20a%20Space%20Force%20developmental%20engineer%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20I%20tell%20them%20about%20my%20day-to-day%20life%2C%20and%20they're%20just%20kind%20of%20dumbfounded%20that%20we%20don't%20have%20mandatory%20PT%20three%20times%20a%20week%20or%20we%20have%20to%20form%20up%20and%20stuff%20like%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20presence%20also%20led%20to%20some%20extra%20attention%20during%20the%20challenges%2C%20with%20many%20soldiers%20reportedly%20calling%20them%20%26quot%3Bspace%20cowboys%26quot%3B%20as%20they%20rucked%20from%20one%20painful%20activity%20to%20the%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLet's%20just%20say%20they%20showed%20us%20some%20extra%20love%20for%20being%20space%20cowboys%2C%26quot%3B%20Savage%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParticipating%20in%20and%20completing%20the%20Army%20Cavalry%20Spur%20Ride%20marks%20the%20latest%20frontier%20that%20the%20Space%20Force's%20men%20and%20women%20have%20conquered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20Space%20Force%20is%20covered%20in%20dust%20as%20the%20light%20from%20sunset%20illuminates%20his%20face%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663a86769686a6f37bfcf696%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22668%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Space%20Force%20spur%20ride%20candidate%20takes%20a%20breather%20before%20continuing%20through%20an%20obstacle%20during%20a%20spur%20ride%20at%20Fort%20Bliss%2C%20Texas.%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20photo%20by%20Spc.%20David%20Poleski%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20two%20Space%20Force%20Guardians%20became%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fdaily-news%2F2024%2F04%2F04%2F2-space-force-guardians-become-services-first-graduates-of-armys-drill-instructor-academy.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efirst%20in%20the%20service%20to%20graduate%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Army's%20Drill%20Instructor%20Academy%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fbase-guide%2Ffort-jackson%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EFort%20Jackson%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20South%20Carolina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fdaily-news%2F2023%2F10%2F17%2Fguardian-gets-ranger-tab-first-ever-achievement-space-force.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESpace%20Force%20Guardian%20Capt.%20Dan%