l%20court%20on%20Tuesday%20seeking%20to%20block%20a%20law%20signed%20by%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20that%20would%20force%20the%20divestiture%20of%20the%20short%20video%20app%20used%20by%20170%20million%20Americans%20or%20ban%20its%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20companies%20filed%20their%20lawsuit%20in%20the%20U.S.%20Court%20of%20Appeals%20for%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20Circuit%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20law%20violates%20the%20U.S.%20Constitution%20on%20a%20number%20of%20grounds%20including%20running%20afoul%20of%20First%20Amendment%20free%20speech%20protections.%20The%20law%2C%20signed%20by%20Biden%20on%20April%2024%2C%20gives%20ByteDance%20until%20Jan.%2019%20to%20sell%20TikTok%20or%20face%20a%20ban.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%20history%2C%20Congress%20has%20enacted%20a%20law%20that%20subjects%20a%20single%2C%20named%20speech%20platform%20to%20a%20permanent%2C%20nationwide%20ban%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20companies%20said%20in%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20and%20U.S.%20Justice%20Department%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20said%20the%20divestiture%20%26quot%3Bis%20simply%20not%20possible%3A%20not%20commercially%2C%20not%20technologically%2C%20not%20legally.%20...%20There%20is%20no%20question%3A%20the%20Act%20(law)%20will%20force%20a%20shutdown%20of%20TikTok%20by%20January%2019%2C%202025%2C%20silencing%20the%20170%20million%20Americans%20who%20use%20the%20platform%20to%20communicate%20in%20ways%20that%20cannot%20be%20replicated%20elsewhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20is%20the%20latest%20move%20by%20TikTok%20to%20keep%20ahead%20of%20efforts%20to%20shut%20it%20down%20in%20the%20United%20States%20as%20companies%20such%20as%20Snap%20and%20Meta%20look%20to%20capitalize%20on%20TikTok's%20political%20uncertainty%20to%20take%20away%20advertising%20dollars%20from%20their%20rival.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDriven%20by%20worries%20among%20U.S.%20lawmakers%20that%20China%20could%20access%20data%20on%20Americans%20or%20spy%20on%20them%20with%20the%20app%2C%20the%20measure%20was%20passed%20overwhelmingly%20in%20Congress%20just%20weeks%20after%20being%20introduced.%20TikTok%20has%20denied%20that%20it%20has%20or%20ever%20would%20share%20U.S.%20user%20data%2C%20accusing%20American%20lawmakers%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20of%20advancing%20%26quot%3Bspeculative%26quot%3B%20concerns%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20prohibits%20app%20stores%20from%20offering%20TikTok%20and%20bars%20internet%20hosting%20services%20from%20supporting%20TikTok%20unless%20ByteDance%20divests%20TikTok%20by%20Jan.%2019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20said%20the%20Chinese%20government%20%26quot%3Bhas%20made%20clear%20that%20it%20would%20not%20permit%20a%20divestment%20of%20the%20recommendation%20engine%20that%20is%20a%20key%20to%20the%20success%20of%20TikTok%20in%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%20The%20companies%20asked%20the%20D.C.%20Circuit%20to%20block%20U.S.%20Attorney%20General%20Merrick%20Garland%20from%20enforcing%20the%20law%20and%20says%20%26quot%3Bprospective%20injunctive%20relief%26quot%3B%20is%20warranted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETikTok%20has%20spent%20%242%20billion%20to%20implement%20measures%20to%20protect%20the%20data%20of%20U.S.%20users%20and%20made%20additional%20commitments%20in%20a%2090-page%20draft%20National%20Security%20Agreement%20developed%20through%20negotiations%20with%20the%20Committee%20on%20Foreign%20Investment%20in%20the%20United%20States%20(CFIUS)%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20pact%20included%20TikTok%20agreeing%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Bshut-down%20option%26quot%3B%20that%20would%20give%20the%20U.S.%20government%20the%20authority%20to%20suspend%20TikTok%20in%20the%20United%20States%20if%20it%20violates%20some%20obligations%2C%20according%20to%20the%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%202022%2C%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20CFIUS%20stopped%20engaging%20in%20meaningful%20discussions%20about%20the%20agreement%2C%20and%20in%20March%202023%20CFIUS%20%26quot%3Binsisted%20that%20ByteDance%20would%20be%20required%20to%20divest%20the%20U.S.%20TikTok%20business.%26quot%3B%20CFIUS%20is%20an%20interagency%20committee%2C%20chaired%20by%20the%20U.S.%20Treasury%20Department%2C%20that%20reviews%20foreign%20investments%20in%20American%20businesses%20and%20real%20estate%20that%20implicate%20national%20security%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBiden%20could%20extend%20the%20Jan.%2019%20deadline%20by%20three%20months%20if%20he%20determines%20ByteDance%20is%20making%20progress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20then-President%20Donald%20Trump%20was%20blocked%20by%20the%20courts%20in%20his%20bid%20to%20ban%20TikTok%20and%20Chinese-owned%20WeChat%2C%20a%20unit%20of%20Tencent%2C%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20Trump%2C%20the%20Republican%20candidate%20challenging%20the%20Democrat%20Biden%20in%20the%20Nov.%205%20U.S.%20election%2C%20has%20since%20reversed%20course%2C%20saying%20he%20does%20not%20support%20a%20ban%20but%20that%20security%20concerns%20need%20to%20be%20addressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20experts%20have%20questioned%20whether%20any%20potential%20buyer%20possesses%20the%20financial%20resources%20to%20buy%20TikTok%20and%20if%20China%20and%20U.S.%20government%20agencies%20would%20approve%20a%20sale.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20move%20the%20TikTok%20source%20code%20to%20the%20United%20States%20%26quot%3Bwould%20take%20years%20for%20an%20entirely%20new%20set%20of%20engineers%20to%20gain%20sufficient%20familiarity%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20four-year%20battle%20over%20TikTok%20is%20a%20significant%20front%20in%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20over%20the%20internet%20and%20technology%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20China.%20In%20April%2C%20Apple%20said%20China%20had%20ordered%20it%20to%20remove%20Meta%20Platforms'%20WhatsApp%20and%20Threads%20from%20its%20App%20Store%20in%20China%20over